text_raw: Our pediatrician was very worried about this kind of oil given to children and presented as "healthy". Max never had some. In a therapeutic ketogenic diet we must be sure of the quality of the products we are feeding with. Max's main fatty sources are coming from animal fats, olive oil, walnut oil, avocado, sesame, pistachio.... and always organic.

[ANGELMAN SYNDROME (AS)]. ‚Äî Ataxia/tremors/laughter outbursts/severe mental retardation. EPIGENETIC cause = paternal UPD. ‚Ä¢ Affects UBE3A function to cause mental retardation. EPIMUTATION (mixed) cause = imprint defect.

[ANGELMAN SYNDROME (AS)]. ‚Äî Ataxia/tremors/laughter outbursts/severe mental retardation. GENETIC cause = maternal 15q deletion or UBE3A mutations. ‚Ä¢ UBE3A ‚Äî ubiquitin protein ligase 3A. - Maternally expressed in brain. ‚Ä¢ Abolished UBE3A function = mental retardation.

Did you enjoy the Sensory Spectacle talks and workshop at the conference? On Tuesday 6th November they have arranged the first conference of its kind all about Interoception. This is an internal sensory system that helps people to know when they are hungry, thirsty, tired or need the toilet. For many of the children and adults we support these messages can be hard to understand and so we therefore may recognise high anxiety levels. The conference brings together some of the best researchers in this area and autism as well as Occupational Therapists to help us learn ways in which we can support these difficulties as well. It is going to be held at The Bridge School in London from 9am - 5.15pm and is ¬£175. There are a couple of parent spaces available too at the price of ¬£75. ~. Then on Thursday 8th November they have a workshop teaching all about Sensory Processing Difficulties. This workshop is called FEEL IT and covers. the importance of our senses,. why we need them for learning,. what Sensory Processing Difficulties are, how we can recognise and understand characteristics of SPD,. how it might feel,. strategies and ideas to support children & adults. This workshop is aimed at everyone - parents, all professionals and students studying in a similar field. It runs from 9.45am - 3pm and is ¬£80pp. Please contact Sensory Spectacle through FB or email hello@sensoryspectacle.co.uk to book.

Our specialist theme for this issue is Rare Employment where we want to highlight the challenges for those affected by rare disease or caring for someone when it comes to maintaining meaningful employment. Have you managed. to work with a company who is willing to be flexible and accommodate your needs? Has your condition led your career in a different path? What top tips. could you give employers that would make it possible for you to get back into the work place? We would welcome any contributions around this theme. Thank you to all of the families that have participated in our study! Purdue University is still recruiting families of children with Angelman syndrome ages 6-48 months to participate in a longitudinal study about early development. Families must reside in the United States. Participation can be completed online and via phone, and families are provided $15 gift card for each assessment. title_raw: Angelman Syndrome Support, Education & Research Trust (ASSERT)
text_raw: As some of you may have noticed, we have relaunched today as AngelmanUK! This is our official page, currently called Angelman Syndrome Support Education and Research Trust will shortly change to AngelmanUK. (This takes up to 3 days).This page AngelmanUK will be where we post the information that we want to share with you. Please like this page to keep up to date with AngelmanUK. Our closed group AngelmanUK Support & Chat is where you can talk to other parents, ask for advice and share experiences. It is open to parents and professionals who have an interest in Angelman Syndrome. https://www.facebook.com/groups/angelmansyndromeuk/. Hopefully you will have receive your newsletters today or tomorrow - let us know what you think! Please bear with us whilst we undergo this transition.

text_raw: *** FRISIUM (clobazam) ***. If you take Frisium(clobazam) tablets these are currently out of stock. SANOFI - the makers of Frisium, are expecting to have more stock week beginning of 6 August. This only affects Frisium made by Sanofi, if you take a generic version of clobazam, there are no supply issues. If you are running short of Frisium, talk to your epilepsy specialist nurse or GP before switching to a generic version of clobazam as this may cause an increase in seizure activity for people with Angelman Syndrome.

title_raw: Angelman Syndrome Support, Education & Research Trust (ASSERT)
text_raw: London Marathon 2018 - on behalf of all the trustees and all of our members, ASSERT would like to say a massive massive thank you to our marathon runners yesterday. Running 26.2 miles is challenging enough, but when its the hottest marathon on record it must have made the race 100 times harder. We are very happy to report all finished in one piece! Please post some photos, we would love to see some of all of you during the event. You've put a huge amount of effort into your training and fundraising and you have all done a fantastic job. We are very grateful to all of you for your dedication over the months. Thank you very much!
Thank you for this opportunity and grateful to have such hard working individuals who care so much for our AS community. Great job!!!
Hope it goes well and you can enjoy it!! Thank You x.

So glad to see there is a walk closer to home this Year! My grandaughter has AS and we will be attending the walk in Albany this year.

Walk Coordinator Spotlight: David & Emmalee Olszewski - Albany, NY. "We would like to spread the word about Angelman Syndrome to improve the educational programming and medical care for individuals with AS. Our son Brady is motivating us to organize the Albany, New York Angelman Syndrome walk. We believe Brady as well as many others with AS have so much to share and so much love to give! We want to be the voice that our son and others do not have. We want to do our part as parents to educate and bring awareness to anyone who will listen." Register for the ASF Walk at www.angelman.org/walk.

title_raw: Angelman Syndrome Support, Education & Research Trust (ASSERT)
text_raw: SILVER SPRING FLING - 25 yrs of ASSERT : IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT - due to circumstances beyond our control the SSF is moving to later in the year. It will now be 10th November. Everything else remains the same, its just the date that has changed. All existing bookings will just be transferred to the new date. A letter will be sent out shortly to inform all of our members. If you were unable to attend in May then hopefully you will now be able to attend in November. Please look out for your letter in the next few weeks.
